annotationA: Suppressor of stem-loop mutation, isoform A; Zinc ion binding; core RNA polymerase binding transcription factor activity. It is involved in the biological process described with: transcription from RNA polymerase II promoter; transcriptional open complex formation at RNA polymerase II promoter; nucleotide-excision repair; promoter clearance from RNA polymerase II promoter; transcription initiation from RNA polymerase II promoter
annotationB: Transcription factor B5 is a subunit of the basal transcription and DNA repair factor TFIIH, which operates in transcription and DNA repair
